Date: Tue, 27 May 2008 13:07:02
From: Rocky Meade [rocky.meade@uwimona.edu.jm]
Subject: SPCL 2009 Winter Conference San Francisco
E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=19-1699.html&submissionid=179561&topicid=3&msgnumber=1  

Full Title: SPCL 2009 Winter Conference San Francisco 
Short Title: SPCL 2009 

Date: 09-Jan-2009 - 10-Jan-2009
Location: San Francisco, California, USA 
Contact Person: Rocky Meade
Meeting Email: rocky.meade@uwimona.edu.jm
Web Site: http://www.mona.uwi.edu/dllp/spcl/Conferences.html 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Language Family(ies): Creole 

Call Deadline: 16-Jun-2008 

Meeting Description:

The Society for Pidgin and Creole Linguistics will meet at the Hilton San
Francisco, California, January 9-10, 2009, in conjunction with the 83rd Annual
Meeting of the Linguistic Society of America. 

Call for Papers

Abstracts on the phonology, morphology, syntax, semantics, lexicon, social
aspects of language, history of the discipline, education or any pertinent issue
involving pidgin and creole languages or other contact languages are invited for
anonymous review by a five member panel. The abstract (including references
and/or examples, if needed) must be no more than 500 words. Include the title at
the top of the abstract, but do not include your name or affiliation. That
information should be submitted separately.

Submit your abstract through EasyChair by June 16, 2008.
Register with EasyChair http://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=spcl2009
Click on ''I have no EasyChair account'' to create one, then proceed to New
Submission. Copy and paste your abstract and title in the given boxes. Be sure
to tick the box ''Abstract Only'', and then ''Submit Paper''. If you are unable
to access EasyChair, then additional submission information is available at the
conference website http://www.mona.uwi.edu/dllp/spcl/Conferences.html

If your abstract is accepted and you are not already a member of SPCL, in good
standing, you must become a member in order to present your paper at the
conference. You do not need to be a member to attend the conference without
presenting a paper, but you are encouraged apply for membership.



	
